Gent Francois Herrebout

als aenden voet deser meerder staen te volgen sij sijn voor mons martin

5 Juny
Londen Jan Kent & comp
sence my last of 2 cur, receaved yours of 13 & 17 past with invoyce of N.7
shipt for rotterdam, and N8 for ostend, I can nott. butt wonder that you
lost the opportunitie for amst, sure, you have no designe in itt yett I do
nott understand the misterie, for I have found you all a longe averse of
shipping for amst, both in london and hull, yett the amsterdammers, have
the best convoy, had you shipped N.7 for amsterdam the goods had been
here, and you might have shipped another pack with spanish clothes for
rotterdam, you make not a word mention of pack whites EE yeallow
marck, pray observe orders, or wee can not be good friends you remitt
mee £200: on pedro vande velde silvus Joos, with I have sent for
acceptance, butt if you will nott remit mee of your owne bills, I will
have none because I will runn no risveque so keep my monney in your
1udd
ordered, and I will not be disappointed because I leave my commissions to you
to avoide writing I have receaved the wishes, as also most pass, of the
goods from hull, which prove vere deare and the 5ƒ cloths, to low prises
and to course to assort mee, so lett your freind att leeds provide better goods and
bestow hull 5ƒ or a pennich, or 2 more, which pray lett be minded, for these
of 4ƒ87 & 4 ƒ 9 are not proper for my customers, here is news as if then
frensh fleet was routed, god grand itt be true whilst I rest
5 Juny
Londen Richard Southell
I have both yours of 13 & 17 past the contents where of are disagreable because
you last like willfulley the opportunitie of shipping for amsterdam for
mease the infortunate pack had not been readdy you might have shipped timely
enough the others spanish cloaths for rest of my order and the more because
I have so herteley recommended you to loose no opportunitie of a convoy, though
you should ship butt 6 on 8 cloathes now I you say with yours of 17 that
you shall ship N.1 for rott & that you doubted not, butt a convoy should be
speedley, and in the meane wile I have advise 4 dayes before befo that the
rotterdams convoy was arrived in the river, att which I wonder you have no
better information, now I am of opinion that, said convoy will depart before
anney other, so ship the 2 pack that way, getting insured the same, for feare
of a worse disaster, tis well you have taken out the culloured mockx and that
you will send mee blaeckx insteed, so lett mee have an other invoyce of the contents
of N.1 as now itt is with the charges and insurance added, I see as yett butt
little apparence of a convoy for ostend, onless itt be granted in england, if you
can meet 5 pack whites EE yeallow marck that are good, white, and withhout
blew streeps, as some are, buy them for mee, butt you must look them well
over, for they are to make religous habits as soon as I have invoyce of the
ordered goods, shall remitt you preventley and in the meane wile, considder upon
the patter you sent mee you must be more rimble in writing and giving advise
what passes, or clee you can not so well please mee, because in these dangerous
times, I longe verey post to heare some thing or other of my intrest the beeffnes
of m vivian is recommended to you whilst I rest
5 Juny
Londen Jan du maistre
en responce a la vre du 13 passe vous aurez eu promt advis j'uns correspondent
a bruges, si nne misfortune ne m'auroit pas empesche, car le 19 du passe quand
ie vous escriva ma derniere ma fmme tomba malade, & mouroit le 29 ditto
c qu'il m'at embarassé beauloup, et empeche encor beaucoup de mes affaires
non obstante i'ay pas oublie de chercher ine correspondent a bruges
